text.section:
Before a license expires, the licensee may renew it for an additional 2-year term, if the licensee:
otherwise is entitled to be licensed;
pays to the Board a renewal fee of:
$70 for a master plumber license or a limited master plumber license;
$35 for a journey plumber license or a limited journey plumber license;
$15 for an apprentice plumber license or apprentice natural gas fitters license;
$35 for a propane gas fitter certificate;
$35 for a master natural gas fitters license; or
$25 for a journeyman natural gas fitters license; and
submits to the Board:
if contracting in the name of the licensee or another person to provide plumbing services, proof of the liability insurance required under § 12-501 of this title; and
a renewal application on the form that the Board provides.
